name: WestJet Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner First Departure from Calgary Airport
description:
After arriving in some nasty weather yesterday, WestJet's first Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner departed their home base here at Calgary International Airport for Toronto-Pearson, where they'll complete their post-delivery checks, as the new widebody hangar in Calgary isn't yet complete. It'll be done in March in time for the new transatlantic flights out of Calgary with the Dreamliner!

Seen here is Tail 901, "Clive Beddoe", under tow out of WestJet's apron, and then making a smoky dual-engine startup on taxiway Foxtrot, taxiing up close on its way to be de-iced, and then making a very light departure off runway 17R. ATC is included throughout, enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
